# SSH key generate  - you only need to do this just the very first time you wanna do smth wiht the shared folder
Open terminal anywhre and execute commands line by line
ssh-keygen -t ed25519 -C "your_email@example.com"_
Press enter 3 times
cat ~/.ssh/id_ed25519.pub
copy the public key and add it to the shared folder in the settings of github

# Steps to download the folder(repository) itself from the web
Inside your chosen folder open terminal and type:
git clone git@github.com:mtelek/IntroProg.git

# Steps to upload your changes to the common folder
Before you upload something, check/ask the others whether they have already uuploaded something what you dont have inside your folder!
If they already uploaded something and you dont have it the process is more complicated.
First use git clone again (its gonna download all of the changes from others)
and than in this folder implement your changes (copy paste you code into this new folder) and than you can continue with the steps below in the new fodler

If no changes were made from others, just use these steps below.
Inside the folder open terminal and than execute git commands line by line:
git status 																#checks whether you folder version is up to date
git add .  																#adds everything that has been changed in the folder (the point at the end means "everyting")
git commit -m "your message in double quotes - what have you changed" 	#you make a new commit, meaning you decide to add the changed files/folders
git push																#you push the changes,meaing you make it official and seeable to everyone

# Steps to get all of the changes others made in the folder
Inside the folder open terminal and than execute git commands line by line:
git pull